ria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hhh1665702793420.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hhh1665702793420.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hhh1665702793420.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hhh1665702793420\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Entity Editor\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Entity Editor enables you to define an Entity and its Fields, Keys, and Relationships.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hhh1665702793420__section_w3412ab1b7b1_w3413ab1b7_w3414ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hhh1665702793420__section_w3415ab1b7b3_w3416ab1b7_w3417ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d511142e60\">\n                       \n Worksheets\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hhh1665702793420__li_d2480e1_d2481e1_d2482e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Define Structure</span>—define the Entity's properties and fields, as well as its subtype entities (if any).\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hhh1665702793420__li_d2483e1_d2484e1_d2485e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Define Keys/Indexes</span>—specify the fields that make up primary and candidate keys, and that will be indexed.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hhh1665702793420__li_d2486e1_d2487e1_d2488e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Define Relationships</span>—establish relationships between the Entity (and its subtypes) , and other entities. Relationships are owned by the Many entity.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hhh1665702793420__li_d2489e1_d2490e1_d2491e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Write Script</span>—define common or\n               default behavior using ProcScript. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hhh1665702793420__section_w3418ab1b7b5_w3419ab1b7_w3420ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d511142e92\">\n                       \n How to\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hhh1665702793420__li_d2492e1_d2493e1_d2494e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ppe1703162040468.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ppe1703162040468.html\" title=\"Modeled entities define the data definitions and default behavior for Uniface components accessing the data.\">Define a Modeled Entity</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hhh1665702793420__li_d2495e1_d2496e1_d2497e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dkp1665702773261.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dkp1665702773261.html\" title=\"Although development objects can be quite different in content and purpose, the way you create, edit and delete them in the Uniface IDE is essentially the same.\">Working with Development Objects</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"hhh1665702793420__fig_w3421ab1b7b5b5b1_w3422ab1b7b5b5_w3423ab1b7b5_w3424ab1b7_w3425ab1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Entity Editor showing Define Structure Worksheet </figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Entity Editor: Define Structure worksheet\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/entityeditor_structure.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"Figure 1. Entity Editor showing Define Structure Worksheet \" id=\"hhh1665702793420__image_v2z_14r_5cc\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/entityeditor_structure.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\"/>\n</figure>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vfy1703055298366.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Modeled Entities</a><p>A Modeled Entity is a main development object that represents a logical data aggregation such as a database table,a collection of records, user interface controls, or other data structure. It is an abstract object that is intended for re-use in other objects, such as components, variables, and parameters.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ula1665702613468.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Entities</a><p>An Entity defines a logical data aggregation. It usually represents a relational database table, but it is possible to define non-database entities for transient data, reusable user interface controls, or other application structures.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528212\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528212\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Entity Editor Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Entity Editor The Entity Editor enables you to define an Entity and its Fields, Keys, and Relationships. Worksheets Define Structure —define the Entity's properties and fields, as well as its subtype entities (if any). Define Keys/Indexes —specify the fields that make up primary and candidate keys, and that will be indexed. Define Relationships —establish relationships between the Entity (and its subtypes) , and other entities. Relationships are owned by the Many entity. Write Script —define common or default behavior using ProcScript. How to Define a Modeled Entity Working with Development Objects Figure 1. Entity Editor showing Define Structure Worksheet Related Links Modeled Entities A Modeled Entity is a main development object that represents a logical data aggregation such as a database table,a collection of records, user interface controls, or other data structure. It is an abstract object that is intended for re-use in other objects, such as components, variables, and parameters. Entities An Entity defines a logical data aggregation. It usually represents a relational database table, but it is possible to define non-database entities for transient data, reusable user interface controls, or other application structures. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}